    - Object selection
      - **Single click**
        - Selects the object and one subelement (edge, face, vertex)

      - **Double click**
        - Selects the object and all its subelements

      - **Multiple selection**
        - Hold `Ctrl` to select several objects or subelements (same or different objects)

      - **Deselect**
        - Click empty space in the 3D View

      - **Selection View panel**
        - Available from the View menu
        - Displays currently selected objects/elements
        - Allows searching and selecting objects directly
  - objects
    - name : default and unmutable
    - label : user-friendly-name
    - placement : position in 3D space
  - <a href="https://wiki.freecad.org/Manual:Parametric_objects" target="_blank">parametric modelling</a>
    - geometry of objects governed by underlying rules and parameters
      - rather than being freely sculpted
      - allow precision and easy modification
      - good to know
        - Recomputation following modification is not always automatic
          - `Edit->Refresh`
        - Circular dependency disallowed
          - `Tools -> Dependency graph`
    - <a href="https://wiki.freecad.org/Scripted_objects" target="_blank">programmable in python</a>


- Document formats
  - `.FCStd`
    - FreeCAD documents format
    - zip-based compound structure : additional safety net
      - akin to LibreOffice
      - allowing direct access to contents
        - troubleshooting
        - data recovery
  - `.STEP`
    - ISO 10303
      - maximum cross-software compability

